    text: "(1) Creditor and debtor may agree that the debtor will pay the creditor a sum of money or provide other material benefit if it fails to perform or is late in performing (contractual penalty).\n\n(2) Unless otherwise agreed, the penalty is deemed agreed for the debtor's delay in performance.\n\n(3) A contractual penalty may not be agreed for monetary obligations.",
