    text: "(1) Pre-contractual negotiations are not binding and either party may break them off at any time.\n\n(2) A party negotiating without intending to conclude a contract is liable for damage caused by the negotiations.\n\n(3) A party that negotiated intending to conclude a contract but abandoned that intention without good cause and thereby caused damage to the other party is also liable.\n\n(4) Unless otherwise agreed, each party bears its own preparation costs and they share joint costs equally.",
